cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper is about neural architecture search, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method for efficient architecture search, which involves optimization and learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The proposed method is applied to image classification tasks, specifically on CIFAR-10 and CIFAR-100 datasets, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves the use of genetic algorithms, which is a subfield of optimization and search algorithms, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the computational efficiency of the proposed method, which can be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
